    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Afton emerged as a separate town in 1857, carved out of the older town of Bainbridge.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4,
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afton%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The town’s name echoes Scotland’s Afton Water, a river celebrated by poet Robert Burns.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
